1)Dengue viruses (types 1, 2, 3 and 4) are RNA viruses of the family Flaviviridiae. They are transmitted from human to human via the mosquito Aedes aegypti. This mosquito bites in the daytime, is adapted to human habitats and has a string preference for human blood. 2)It breeds in relatively clean water stored for drinking or washing purposes, and in rainwater that collects in manmade containers.
3)Most primary dengue virus infections in children and many in adults are silent. Dengue infection presents clinically as three overlapping syndromes.
4) Undifferentiated fever, Dengue fever syndrome and Dengue hemorrhagic fever/Dengue shock syndrome (DHF/DSS).
5) The symptoms of overt dengue infections are common to many acute viral, bacterial and parasitic infections.
6) Elevated Hematocrit and hypotension (or narrow pulse pressure) are unique to Dengue infections. Presumptive diagnosis of dengue fever or DHF requires a careful travel history to establish possible exposure to dengue virus infection.
7) Antibodies against dengue viruses can be detected 5 to 7 days after onset of symptoms.

values.value:
Dengue virus [Serotype 1, 2, 3 & 4] is a RNA virus of the Flaviviridae family. Transmitted to the human by the bite of mosquito  Aedes Aegypti, which  bites in the daytime  & has a stringe preference for human blood. Most of the time the dengue infection in children & adults remain silent. Dengue infection can present as   Dengue  fever,   Dengue hemorrhagic fever  or more severe form as  Dengue shock syndrome [DSS] .
Classical   DSS   may present as a high fever, thrombocytopenia, elevated hematocrit and hypotension.
Ig M Antibodies against Dengue virus can be detected early after the onset of symptoms. Ig G antibodies are detected from the 5 the day of illness, reach to peak level at 2-3 months following initial infection. Ig M antibodies are often not detectable after the second infection with another serotype. Ig G antibodies usually persist throughout life. After a second infection with another serotype Ig G antibodies rise of over 10 fold concentration is usually found.
